        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- SOUND & ATMOSPHERE: round 2 restructure — the FENDI video and both
         SoundCloud tracks now sit as three equal small thumbnails in one
         row (matching the Gamma reference's own layout, which this had
         drifted from into three stacked full-width embeds that dominated
         the viewport), with the descriptive paragraph below the row
         instead of above it, also matching the reference's actual order. -->
    <section class="fv-section fade-item">
      <h2>Sound &amp; Atmosphere</h2>
      <p class="fv-instruction">Explore selected visual and audio projects by clicking the images below.</p>
      <div class="fv-embed-row">
        <div class="fv-embed-item fv-embed-item-video">
          <button
            type="button"
            class="fv-embed-facade"
            data-embed-type="video"
            data-embed-src={`https://www.youtube.com/embed/${YOUTUBE_VIDEO_ID}?autoplay=1`}
            data-embed-title="Maya Fourteen, FENDI & GT Home / Pininfarina video set"
            aria-label="Play video: Maya Fourteen, FENDI & GT Home / Pininfarina video set"
          >
            <img src={`https://img.youtube.com/vi/${YOUTUBE_VIDEO_ID}/maxresdefault.jpg`} alt="" loading="lazy" width="1280" height="720" />
            <span class="fv-embed-play" aria-hidden="true"></span>
          </button>
        </div>
        {soundcloudTracks.map((track, i) => (
          <div class="fv-embed-item fv-embed-item-audio">
            <button
              type="button"
              class="fv-embed-facade"
              data-embed-type="audio"
              data-embed-src={track.embedSrc}
              data-embed-title={track.title}
              aria-label={`Play track: ${track.title}`}
            >
              {soundcloudThumbs[i] && <img src={soundcloudThumbs[i]!} alt="" loading="lazy" width="500" height="500" />}
              <span class="fv-embed-play" aria-hidden="true"></span>
            </button>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
      <p>
        MAYA's work extends beyond clubs, radios and festivals, into carefully selected
        audiovisual projects and cultural settings worldwide. Alongside her club and festival
        activity, she has developed bespoke sets and sound narratives for fashion, private
        events, and brand-driven environments, adapting her musical language to context
        without compromising identity.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- PRESS ASSETS -->
    <section class="fv-section fade-item">
      <h2>Press Assets</h2>
      <div class="fv-photo-grid">
        <div class="fv-photo-frame"><img src={images.fashionPress1.src} width={images.fashionPress1.width} height={images.fashionPress1.height} alt="Maya Fourteen, editorial portrait in a black textured outfit" loading="lazy" /></div>
        <div class="fv-photo-frame"><img src={images.fashionPress2.src} width={images.fashionPress2.width} height={images.fashionPress2.height} alt="Maya Fourteen, portrait seated on rustic wooden steps" loading="lazy" /></div>
        <div class="fv-photo-frame"><img src={images.fashionPress3.src} width={images.fashionPress3.width} height={images.fashionPress3.height} alt="Maya Fourteen, portrait against a corrugated metal wall" loading="lazy" /></div>
        <div class="fv-photo-frame"><img src={images.fashionPress4.src} width={images.fashionPress4.width} height={images.fashionPress4.height} alt="Maya Fourteen, portrait in the desert at golden hour" loading="lazy" /></div>
      </div>
      <p>High-resolution images available for promotional use. All photos copyright protected.</p>
      <div class="fv-download-actions">
        <a class="cta-button cta-button-solid" href="https://drive.google.com/open?id=1Y0dyWs18uc7w8QbKFj_pbmrpeX81bu_j" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Download Press Kit</a>
        <a class="cta-button cta-button-outline" href="https://drive.google.com/open?id=1XacZsWwys1ieA5C3hLZzSoFWPFS_yh2z" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Download Full Artist EPK</a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- DISCOVER MAYA: round 2 — dropped the colored rounded-square badges
         (those only existed to mimic the Gamma reference) for a plain,
         monochrome icon row: no boxes, no per-platform brand colors, just
         icon + label, matching the rest of this page's minimal aesthetic.
         Website is first (globe icon, inline SVG so it doesn't need a new
         icon-font style loaded — see the file header's "no new
         dependencies" note), then Instagram, YouTube, SoundCloud, LinkedIn. -->
    <section class="fv-section fv-discover fade-item">
      <h2>Discover MAYA</h2>
      <div class="fv-discover-row">
        <a
          class="fv-discover-item"
          href="https://mayafourteen.com"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener"
          title="Website"
          aria-label="Website (opens in a new tab)"
        >
          <span class="fv-discover-icon" aria-hidden="true">
            <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5">
              <circle cx="12" cy="12" r="9" />
